WEBVTT

00:03.650 --> 00:04.131
Good morning.

00:06.554 --> 00:07.795
We are finishing up the year.

00:07.815 --> 00:10.659
This is the last Sunday of 2025.

00:11.640 --> 00:13.742
All right.

00:13.803 --> 00:23.595
And before we get into 2026, though, it's a wonderful opportunity to take a look back and to remember some things, to think about this year.

00:24.456 --> 00:32.786
As I was listening to the scripture read from the back there, I was thinking to myself,

00:33.282 --> 00:45.296
The Israelite people in this moment in time, the reading of Joshua 4, what's really happening there is they've been through the wilderness for 40 years, right?

00:45.796 --> 00:49.761
And then they finally get into the Promised Land, but they're not quite in yet.

00:50.121 --> 00:53.145
They're near it or they're close, but they're not quite there.

00:53.185 --> 00:57.810
And there's any number of ways they could tell their own story.

00:58.178 --> 00:58.438
Right?

00:58.819 --> 01:03.363
They could have looked back and said, boy, God nearly left us for dead.

01:03.403 --> 01:08.649
We almost died back there, but we eked our way through it.

01:09.189 --> 01:10.210
And now here we are.

01:11.111 --> 01:12.993
This, of course, is not how they tell their own story.

01:13.013 --> 01:18.959
They did nearly die back there, but they told a story of faithfulness.

01:20.220 --> 01:25.906
As you think about your own year 2025, like there are any number of ways you can tell your own story.

01:26.274 --> 01:32.662
You can think back over the course of this year and you might be tempted to say, I almost died back there.

01:32.843 --> 01:38.410
Or you can tell the story of God's faithfulness in your life too.

01:39.411 --> 01:42.555
The question is, how are you going to tell your own story?

01:43.697 --> 01:50.706
The time we're in right now, this period that sits right before the new year and it's after Christmas,

01:50.818 --> 01:52.881
might be called a liminal space.

01:53.081 --> 01:59.911
A liminal space is simply the space that is like, it's kind of your front door, but it's sort of in the house.

01:59.971 --> 02:01.153
It's sort of out of the house.

02:01.213 --> 02:01.894
It's not clear.

02:02.134 --> 02:03.536
It's a transition space.

02:04.838 --> 02:10.165
You have no doubt been through a transition or a liminal space any number of times in your life.

02:10.906 --> 02:16.434
If you, for example, graduated from high school, but you're not yet in college,

02:17.058 --> 02:18.099
That's a liminal space.

02:18.159 --> 02:25.909
If you've moved from one city to another and you've moved, but you're not quite there yet, that is definitely a liminal space.

02:27.171 --> 02:46.194
If, like me, when you, well, I was a junior in high school, moving my senior year to another state, I experienced a liminal space in life where you can do some reflection and you can ask interesting questions.

02:46.338 --> 02:50.963
such as, well, who was I for the last three years of high school?

02:52.144 --> 02:52.865
Who am I?

02:52.905 --> 02:56.528
And then the better question yet is, who do I want to be?

02:56.568 --> 02:58.971
In what's about to happen here?

02:59.031 --> 03:02.835
In this senior year, I've got new friends and a new place.

03:02.895 --> 03:05.057
I can totally reinvent myself.

03:06.358 --> 03:07.940
Have you experienced this before?

03:07.980 --> 03:09.301
You probably have.

03:09.421 --> 03:13.906
Maybe if you're new to the area, it's moving here.

03:14.146 --> 03:20.415
Who do you want to be in Northern Virginia that you weren't in South Dakota or wherever you're coming from?

03:21.736 --> 03:23.058
That's a liminal space.

03:23.559 --> 03:27.865
And this is precisely where the people find themselves in Joshua 4.

03:28.125 --> 03:29.968
Let's go ahead and read some of this again.

03:30.008 --> 03:31.169
We won't read the whole thing.

03:31.189 --> 03:37.458
But if we skip kind of toward the end of this passage, we see the following.

03:37.954 --> 03:55.941
We see in verse five, Joshua says to them, Pass on before the ark of the Lord your God into the midst of the Jordan and take up each of you a stone upon his shoulder according to the number of the tribes of the people of Israel, that this may be a sign among you.

03:55.981 --> 04:01.930
When your children ask in time to come, what do these stones mean to you?

04:01.990 --> 04:04.434
Then you shall tell them.

04:05.314 --> 04:10.099
Tell them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off before the Ark of the Covenant of the Lord.

04:10.779 --> 04:15.003
When it passed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off.

04:15.464 --> 04:21.450
So these stones shall be to the people of Israel a memorial forever.

04:21.490 --> 04:23.832
These are memory stones.

04:24.273 --> 04:34.002
Apparently they're pretty big, big enough anyway, to like warrant someone walking by seeing the 12 stones and asking,

04:34.082 --> 04:39.588
That means what's happening here with these 12 huge stones.

04:40.809 --> 04:44.654
And then someone says, well, that was when we first got here.

04:45.575 --> 04:49.379
We traversed 40 years through the desert.

04:50.120 --> 04:52.863
Half of us or more died along the way.

04:52.943 --> 05:00.031
And it took a whole generation, but then God saw fit to part the waters.

05:00.171 --> 05:02.834
One more time, this time the Jordan,

05:03.426 --> 05:07.933
to allow us to walk through and to bring us into the promised land.

05:08.574 --> 05:11.139
And it was the beginning of our life together.

05:12.881 --> 05:16.628
And it's all memorialized in these 12 big stones.

05:19.432 --> 05:24.400
I'm going to imagine that you have some memorials in your house, whether you realize it or not.

05:24.961 --> 05:30.450
Nick Max, that sit around maybe your living room or your kitchen, somewhere in your home,

05:30.658 --> 05:35.083
sits something that when you look at it, you remember something.

05:36.144 --> 05:59.410
For me, it's a lot of things, actually, but one, there's a piece of art that sits on the wall of my living room, and it's a piece of art that we bought in 2007 on a trip to Europe before we ever had kids, before the world changed dramatically, and we were in Florence, and we bought this piece of art to remind us of this beautiful trip that we had together.

06:00.354 --> 06:01.299
Or Kendall every year.

06:02.003 --> 06:04.456
She buys ornaments for every one of our kids.

06:05.240 --> 06:07.954
And the ornament has the date on it or the year on it.

06:08.258 --> 06:17.929
And she's very thoughtful with these, and she buys something that has to do with the significance of that year for that child.

06:17.989 --> 06:32.786
And so I can imagine 20 years from now, as those children are in their 30s, and they're picking up these ornaments to put them on their tree, and they're remembering, oh, this was the year I graduated from high school, or this was the year.

06:32.898 --> 06:39.365
that I was nine years old and I happened to love soccer and I loved singing and playing the drums.

06:39.485 --> 06:42.388
And so these are memorials.

06:42.768 --> 06:44.270
We remember things.

06:44.370 --> 06:46.212
And it's important to remember, right?

06:46.252 --> 06:52.118
The question is, I'm a pastor and you're in a church.

06:52.939 --> 06:55.802
And so I'm supposed to draw you into the things of faith.

06:57.003 --> 06:59.666
And so the question is, do you have any memorials

07:00.162 --> 07:02.985
to the faith journey that you've been on.

07:03.846 --> 07:07.590
Like what are those things in your house or in your office?

07:08.251 --> 07:21.765
Maybe it's in your Bible that like reminds you, when you see it, you say to yourself, oh yeah, this was the time that God showed up in this really powerful way and I don't want to forget it.

07:24.188 --> 07:30.034
The scriptures are quite clear that we are supposed to remember.

07:30.914 --> 07:32.276
We are not to forget.

07:33.318 --> 07:36.803
It's actually more prevalent than I even thought it was.

07:36.904 --> 07:56.114
And so I want to share with you a number of the passages where God commands us to remember and let this be a warning shot that you should leave this place remembering and thinking back over the course of your year, the ways in which your life has been shaped

07:56.290 --> 08:06.608
But again, this being a church and all, like the way in which God has showed up in your life in 2025, that you are not going to forget.

08:07.770 --> 08:09.273
It starts in Exodus 13.

08:10.134 --> 08:21.554
Moses says to the people, remember this day in which you came out from Egypt out of the house of slavery for by a strong hand, the Lord brought you out from this place.

08:21.826 --> 08:36.085
or in Deuteronomy 4-9, only take care and keep your soul diligently lest you forget the things that your eyes have seen and lest they depart from your heart all the days of your life.

08:36.846 --> 08:40.891
Make them known to your children and your children's children.

08:40.952 --> 08:51.826
Don't forget, but don't even let your kids forget and don't let their kids forget the kinds of things that God has done in your life and in your ancestors' lives.

08:52.162 --> 09:08.226
or Deuteronomy 8, 2, you shall remember the whole way that the Lord, your God, has led you these 40 years in the wilderness that He might humble you, testing you to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep His commandment or not.

09:09.548 --> 09:15.657
Moving forward in Scripture, Joshua now, this is our passage for the day, 4, 6 to 7.

09:16.218 --> 09:21.426
This may be a sign among you when your children ask in time to come, what do these stones mean?

09:21.730 --> 09:26.876
You shall say to them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off before the ark of the covenant.

09:27.397 --> 09:31.362
So these stones shall be to the people of Israel, a memorial.

09:32.343 --> 09:35.887
They'll help you remember, or first chronicles, 1612.

09:37.029 --> 09:43.036
Remember the wondrous works that he has done, his miracles and his judgments that he uttered.

09:43.877 --> 09:49.244
Psalm 77, I will remember the deeds of the Lord.

09:49.604 --> 09:51.186
Yes, I will remember.

09:51.362 --> 10:02.476
Your wonders of old, Psalm 103, 2, bless the Lord, O my soul, and don't forget all of the things that he has done.

10:04.138 --> 10:09.885
Psalm 105, remember the wondrous works that he has done, his miracles and the judgments he uttered.

10:10.827 --> 10:14.171
Psalm 143, I remember the days of old.

10:14.992 --> 10:16.814
I meditate on all that you've done.

10:17.355 --> 10:19.858
I ponder the work of your hand.

10:20.578 --> 10:21.500
and Isaiah 46-9.

10:22.942 --> 10:24.585
Remember the former things of old.

10:25.206 --> 10:26.488
Remember the former things.

10:27.269 --> 10:29.312
For I am God and there is no other.

10:29.873 --> 10:31.776
I am God and there is none like me.

10:33.700 --> 10:47.282
The call to remember is appropriate again at this time in the year as we're about to head into 2026 and you're about to make some New Year's resolutions

10:47.842 --> 10:52.968
It's probably a good idea to look back and ask, how did I do this year?

10:54.150 --> 10:56.012
How did those resolutions go this year?

10:57.373 --> 10:59.516
Or maybe you're thinking to yourself, you know what?

11:00.177 --> 11:01.699
It's been an awful year.

11:02.099 --> 11:03.921
It's been super tough.

11:03.941 --> 11:06.444
It sure feels like I'm out here all alone.

11:07.786 --> 11:12.011
I would encourage you to ask of God and of yourself.

11:12.992 --> 11:17.778
Is that really true of the whole year, this whole year, 2026?

11:18.114 --> 11:19.736
Have you been alone all that time?

11:20.696 --> 11:26.162
Or are you just in a season of darkness that's shown up for a short time and it too shall pass?

11:29.345 --> 11:33.309
As many of you know, I took a sabbatical this summer and it was a wonderful thing.

11:34.770 --> 11:39.014
One of the things I got to do on my sabbatical was to spend a little time alone.

11:39.515 --> 11:47.282
And as I spent time alone, I began to think back on my own past and where I've come from.

11:48.002 --> 11:52.468
and where I'm going to, a liminal space of its own kind, actually.

11:53.510 --> 12:11.394
And as I began to think back, there were some really tough years, and there was one in particular, 2012, that I won't go into detail with, but it was the year I was graduating with a PhD, but I was unable to find a job in this year.

12:11.434 --> 12:17.362
And I had worked very hard to that point, and I felt abandoned and alone.

12:18.018 --> 12:19.480
I felt abandoned by God.

12:19.520 --> 12:31.296
And I had this moment that I remember very distinctly where I'm shouting out to God and I'm saying, God, if you are real, I need you to show up now in a powerful way.

12:33.199 --> 12:35.282
That moment stuck with me for years.

12:36.784 --> 12:38.586
But for some reason, I forgot.

12:39.828 --> 12:41.370
I forgot how it got answered.

12:41.911 --> 12:44.274
And I want to make sure you know how it got answered.

12:44.834 --> 12:49.639
You see, I was looking back, we used to keep a blog, back when blogs were things.

12:50.780 --> 12:52.982
And it was, sure enough, still on the internet.

12:53.142 --> 12:53.923
So I found it.

12:53.943 --> 13:01.931
And I remembered back to the moment where I had shouted at God and said, like, I need you.

13:03.952 --> 13:06.955
And then I started reading the blog posts around that time.

13:06.995 --> 13:13.842
And what I came to realize was that within two weeks, I had

13:13.954 --> 13:22.626
taken like a mini sabbatical or like a day retreat where God showed up in a really, really powerful way.

13:23.787 --> 13:34.922
And it was one of these moments of life where like I knew that God was present in that moment, not because like I felt, you know, the good feelings.

13:35.082 --> 13:40.610
I did sort of, but because something like truly miraculous happened.

13:41.831 --> 13:43.954
Like there was a miracle in my life.

13:44.450 --> 13:55.427
where someone used the exact phrase and the words and the whole thing that I had been doing that day and they gave it back to me in a way that I thought, that's impossible.

13:55.447 --> 13:56.408
How do you know this?

13:56.468 --> 13:57.630
Were you following me?

13:57.750 --> 14:00.735
Were you snooping in on what I was doing?

14:00.775 --> 14:05.482
And I remember feeling a sense of, this is gonna be okay.

14:05.642 --> 14:06.904
Things are going to be okay.

14:07.565 --> 14:13.554
And then two weeks after that, I got a call and I got an interview

14:14.114 --> 14:16.257
And I got a job.

14:16.277 --> 14:19.100
And I remember thinking, okay, I feel alone.

14:20.522 --> 14:23.806
I feel abandoned, but that's not the whole story.

14:24.507 --> 14:26.029
And I got his presence still.

14:27.171 --> 14:28.712
And I just needed to remember.

14:30.915 --> 14:40.087
And so on the sabbatical, as I was digging through my own past, I asked myself, how could you forget?

14:41.529 --> 14:42.610
How could you forget?

14:44.354 --> 14:52.023
And I guess I'm here to ask you, is there something in your life where God has shown up in like a really powerful way?

14:52.123 --> 14:55.027
Maybe it is this year, but maybe it's deeper than that.

14:56.148 --> 15:02.876
And you've somehow forgotten, you know, encourage you as the Scriptures do over and over and over again.

15:02.916 --> 15:07.922
Remember, remember lest you forget.

15:10.850 --> 15:18.459
Our brains are unfortunately wired to remember the bad things much more easily than the good things.

15:20.542 --> 15:30.414
The bad things in life are like Velcro and they just kind of stick and then the good things are often like Teflon and they just slide right off and they're easily forgotten.

15:31.315 --> 15:33.418
And it's why we need to build memorials.

15:34.079 --> 15:39.826
It's why we need to put things around our house to remind us of the good things

15:40.002 --> 15:44.146
of life, yes, but the good things that God has done in our lives.

15:45.287 --> 15:55.978
I would encourage you not to leave today, not to allow the sun to go down today without remembering something, something good that God has done in your life.

15:56.999 --> 16:03.125
If you want to be a person of faith, you must remember God's faithfulness to you.

16:03.165 --> 16:08.370
If you want to be a person of joy, you must remember

16:08.482 --> 16:10.104
the joy in your life.

16:10.904 --> 16:20.094
If you want to be a person of hope, somebody who's hopeful about what's coming, you must be a person who remembers the reasons for hope.

16:21.816 --> 16:26.781
In some ways, it all comes back to Mary and her magnifying glass from a few sermons ago.

16:26.801 --> 16:33.227
It's a question of what am I going to put my magnifying glass over in this last year or in my life?

16:33.288 --> 16:35.730
How am I going to tell the story of my life?

16:36.162 --> 16:42.011
Am I going to tell the story where all these bad things just keep happening to me and it's a bad life?

16:42.952 --> 16:51.344
Or am I going to put the magnifying glass over the ways in which God has been faithful in my life again and again and again?

16:53.888 --> 16:58.395
Perhaps the most important passage on memory comes to us from Luke 22, 19.

17:00.137 --> 17:05.906
Jesus himself reminds us to remember he took bread

17:06.594 --> 17:14.127
And when he had given thanks, he broke it and gave it to them saying, this is my body, which is given for you.

17:14.768 --> 17:20.518
And then he says, what's etched right there, do this in remembrance of me.

17:21.600 --> 17:23.043
Don't forget.

17:24.545 --> 17:25.347
Remember me.

17:26.128 --> 17:27.390
Remember what I've done.

17:28.011 --> 17:31.858
Remember how I've poured out my life for your life.

17:35.682 --> 17:36.964
Today, I come bearing gifts.

17:38.967 --> 17:42.271
The gift is actually a recycled gift.

17:42.331 --> 17:44.074
It's the ones you gave me.

17:44.875 --> 17:47.398
For the last week, I've been asking you for photos.

17:48.320 --> 17:56.952
And the photos are a snapshot of the life of Southrun Baptist Church over the course of 2025.

17:58.714 --> 18:04.242
Before I show you these things, though, to kind of help jog your memory

18:04.386 --> 18:24.229
of where we've been as a church this year, I thought I'd go through a litany of things that we've done, where we've built bonds together, where you and I have shown up and built a spiritual life together, where we've served the community together.

18:24.269 --> 18:32.338
And so I'm labeling these are four stones that we've built this year.

18:32.994 --> 18:36.158
The first is the stone of spiritual growth.

18:36.979 --> 18:40.424
These are the things, some of them, that we've done.

18:40.925 --> 18:43.969
We started with a week of prayer in January.

18:44.429 --> 18:46.512
We learned how to bless others.

18:47.093 --> 18:50.377
And I imagine that many of you still know how to say it with me right now.

18:50.417 --> 18:56.406
We began with prayer, we listened, we eat, we serve, we share.

18:56.466 --> 19:02.674
We spent 30 weeks on the Believe series, learning to think, act,

19:02.946 --> 19:04.568
and live like Jesus.

19:05.449 --> 19:11.377
We gathered around the table on Wednesday nights for dinner for the first time in a few years.

19:12.118 --> 19:17.445
And most importantly, we saw five people follow Jesus into the waters of baptism.

19:18.507 --> 19:21.931
This is the stone of people being transformed.

19:23.173 --> 19:26.898
The second stone is the stone of radical hospitality.

19:27.394 --> 19:30.017
We completed the elevator project.

19:30.117 --> 19:35.462
If there was like nothing else that we did this year, that felt like a huge weight off.

19:36.603 --> 19:41.087
We ensured that everyone, regardless of mobility, has a seat at the table.

19:41.728 --> 19:47.534
We welcomed hundreds of family to the Easter egg hunt, over 500 neighbors to our trunk retreat.

19:48.134 --> 19:52.779
We handed out Bibles and a gospel in a box to dozens of people.

19:53.760 --> 19:55.922
We are trying to be a city on a hill.

19:56.450 --> 19:58.132
with our lights shining bright.

19:59.273 --> 20:03.096
The third stone is the stone of compassion and care.

20:04.197 --> 20:07.921
There is a lot of need in Fairfax County, it turns out.

20:08.682 --> 20:14.367
And so through power packs, we provided 600 weekend meals for hungry students.

20:14.968 --> 20:18.231
We collected hundreds of pounds of food for Echo.

20:18.912 --> 20:22.435
We stood with the vulnerable through our assist pregnancy center.

20:23.296 --> 20:25.618
And we literally provided warmth during

20:25.698 --> 20:28.120
a week for the hypothermia shelter.

20:29.302 --> 20:35.468
God calls us to minister to the week and to the lowly and you showed up to do that.

20:37.210 --> 20:40.993
The fourth stone is the stone of sending and support.

20:42.134 --> 20:53.746
Finally, we looked beyond our walls and we sent 21 care packages to our college students and 73 shoeboxes around the world with Operation Christmas Child

20:54.498 --> 21:05.832
The generosity we showed was over $11,000 for supporting local and international missions from Dresden, Germany to Marymount University.

21:06.613 --> 21:15.343
We gave $20,000 to support our networks and the faithfulness of this small church is now echoing around the globe.

21:17.386 --> 21:20.470
I am proud of who we are and what we've accomplished.

21:21.131 --> 21:23.954
And most importantly, what God has done

21:24.546 --> 21:25.007
through you.

21:27.229 --> 21:31.434
The ways in which you've shown up this year is worth remembering.

21:32.916 --> 21:45.171
It's worth taking a moment to stop, to think back before we rush into the next year, and to just simply remember what God has done in the life of our church.

21:46.113 --> 21:50.578
So without further ado, we have a slideshow.

22:16.322 --> 22:16.948
Having hair.

23:03.874 --> 23:04.691
of God.

32:23.810 --> 32:33.714
Let's all stand and thank the Lord for this past year, for His grace is mercy and His amazing love and the joy He brings for this time of period.

36:44.802 --> 36:45.983
Thank you for coming today.

36:46.023 --> 36:51.049
As you, you know, finish up the year and you head into the new year.

36:52.090 --> 36:52.691
I'm serious.

36:53.652 --> 36:54.332
Take a minute.

36:54.833 --> 36:55.914
Take a few minutes.

36:55.934 --> 36:57.416
Like think back over your life.

36:58.437 --> 37:00.339
Think back over this year.

37:00.359 --> 37:05.525
And simply ask, where have I seen God on the moon?

37:05.545 --> 37:06.285
Remember it.

37:07.307 --> 37:09.028
Find a way to remember it.

37:09.669 --> 37:14.194
Take a stone or an ornament or something.

37:14.914 --> 37:19.148
put it somewhere in your life so that you don't forget.

37:19.168 --> 37:23.602
As we go out today, we do have a very happy new year and go in the peace of Christ.

